                            ############
                            Installation
                            ############
@WORDWRAP

How to install midiIn:

  It is very simple, you probably have already done it.

  You have to unpack the archive file (what you probably did).
  midiIn.lha archive should (@{"and must" LINK LEGAL}) contain:

    midiIn            89332 - the main program
    midiIn.info        7177 - its icon
    midiIn.guide      29804 - this documentation
    midiIn.guide.info  2608 - guide's icon
    midiIn.pref          50 - a default prefs file
    projects/         <dir> - an empty directory to store Your projects in
    midiIn.sig          528 - md5sum of all files signed with my secret @{"PGP" LINK AUTORS 11} keyring
     to get my public keyring @{"mail me" LINK AUTORS 3}, or you can finger the same address as well.
    libs/reqtools.library
    libs/midi.library

  @{b}@{u}If you don't have those two libraries installed yet, copy them to your
  LIBS: directory.@{ub}@{uu}

  What you should know:

  No assigns nor environment variables are needed for midiIn.
  The configuration file is saved in the same directory, the main
  program is in ('PROGDIR:midiIn.pref').
  Configuration file contains: sound @{"preferences" LINK ADVANCED 12}, default @{"paths" LINK DEALING 18}
  to projects and samples and default @{"sample list" LINK HOWTO 83}.
  The program doesn't need this file to operate.

  @{b}midiIn requires both: reqtools.library and midi.library to be in LIBS:
  directory.@{ub}

